wiki.text:
'AUX' or 'Aux' may refer to:

* An abbreviation of the word “Auxiliary”
* A/UX, a Unix-like operating system produced by Apple
* Aux (TV channel), a Canadian music TV channel
* , a DOS device typically assigned to the first serial port (COM1:)
* AUX (CONFIG.SYS directive), a setting to override the default assignment for
  the AUX: device under DR-DOS
* Auxin, a class of plant hormones and morphogens, or associated molecules such
  as auxin influx transporters (e.g. AUX1) and the Aux/IAA early auxin
  responsive transcription factor family (e.g. AUX22).
* Aux/IAA repressors, a class of early auxin responsive transcription
  factors in plants
